      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/validation/stiffness-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Construct stiffness QoI comparison — FEA vs. bench (N=11)",
      "description": "Predicted construct stiffness from the FEA ensemble was compared against all 11 experimental specimens. Mean experimental stiffness was 312.4 N/mm (SD 18.7 N/mm). FEA ensemble mean was 307.1 N/mm. Percentage difference of 1.7%, well within the 10% acceptance bound. E/uval ratio computed as 0.41, below the 1.96 threshold. The comparison was executed by the FDA CDRH Solid Mechanics Group using Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2 on the validated HPC cluster (cluster validation certificate HPC-2022-004). Mesh independence was confirmed at element count 487,000 (GCI < 0.8%). Material properties were drawn from certified titanium alloy coupon testing (lot-matched to production screws). All boundary conditions replicated ASTM F1717 fixture geometry to within 0.05 mm tolerance. Statistical analysis followed ASME V&V 40-2018 Appendix D. The result is considered a strong confirmation of model adequacy for stiffness prediction.",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/data/bench-test-lab1-n6"
    },
